-- Vedanta Resources Unit Calls Bids to Operate 1,200 MW Power Plant in India
-- Archana Chaudhary
-- 2010-06-29T04:33:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/vedanta-resources-unit-calls-bids-to-operate-1-200-mw-power-plant-in-india.html

          
          
             Vedanta Resources Plc ’s Bharat
Aluminium Co. has called bids to operate a 1,200-megawatt coal-
fired power plant it is building in eastern India, according to
an advertisement in India’s Economic Times today.  
 The company, known as Balco, is seeking bids for the
operation and maintenance of four units of 300 megawatts each at
its aluminum complex at Korba in Chhattisgarh state.  
 Submission of offers is open for 10 days starting today,
according to the advertisement.  
